<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7425> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7425" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Pr. 42? A candidate for the praetorship of 42 (Cic. Fam. 11.16.3, 17.1), later referred to as a praetorius (Plin. NH 7.173; Val. Max. 1.8.12). On his aedileship in 45, see MRR 2.307; Sumner, Phoenix 25, 1971, 361; S. Treggiari, Phoenix 27, 1973, 245253. Delete the notice of a praetorship in 43 in MRR 2.338. (RS, CP; TJC)\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6145> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6145" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Plin. NH 7.173, praetorio viro; a candidate in 43 (Cic. Fam. 11.16.3, and 17. 1)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6035> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6035" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "A candidate in 44 (Cic. Fam. 11. 16.2, and 17. 1), later referred to as a praetorius (Plin. NH 7.173)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5883> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5883" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "He received letters from Caesar urging him to rush preparations for the Ludi Romani (Cic. Att. 13.45.1; Fam. 11.17.1, cf. 16.3). An Aedile of the Plebs, because the curule magistrates, with the exception of Caesar himself as Consul without a colleague, were not elected until Caesar's return from Spain (Dio 43.47-48)." .
